Wildrider considered the irony of what Dominijoe said, he then too burst
into a large grin, but this one wasnt friendly, or patronizing, this one
had a sinister look to it, and the twinkle in Wildrider's eye followed
along to give the impression that he wasnt thinking of pleasant things.
On the verge of his cackling laughter he spoke. "I don't know Cyclonus,
your too trusting, but I do know," he broke, to spit a gob of oil on the
ground, it made a digusting splat. "That the ship will make great scrap
meta'," he pointed his gun threateningly, as his expression changed, "as
will any Maxis, or Autobrats, ain't that right my Decepticon comerades?"
he asked, thrusting out his fist.

(you know, to give some knuckle. Wildrider dosent believe in hand
shakes).
